comment: Added Play Store link to README
Fixed divider height when removing divider drawable
Proper scrollbarStyle in Google Card example
Use of NineOldAndroids library to keep support from API lvl 1
Removed setAlpha() method that requires API 11.
Created option to choose between PropertyValues or animation resources
Removed NineOldAndroids library dependency, added as jar
Fixed hiding of views before animation start
Fixed delay when stacking multiple AnimationAdapters on top of eachother
Added option to set animation duration
Pass listview through to all BaseAdapterDecorators
AnimationAdapters now don't hide the dividers anymore.
SwipeToDismiss example now works on whole row width.
Fixed height problems when using list items with different heights in combination with swipe to dismiss, thanks to Tony Owen. Fixes #2
Added swipe to dismiss to Google cards example
Use a copy of given positions collection
Removed scalein from google cards due to performance issues on scaling imageview.
Not requiring ArrayAdapter for AnimateDismiss; Using OnDismissCallback for AnimateDismiss
Wider text to better show animations.
Working implementation of Contextual Undo pattern
Use position for callback instead of item
Before canceling current animation, check if new animation would be for current animation. If so, don't cancel. Should fix #5
Removed fading edge on pre-ICS devices in the GoogleCardsActivity. Fixes #8
Take GridView in account when calculating delays
Tweaked minFlingVelocity in swipe dismiss listener
Added Javadoc to ContextualUndoAdapter and ContextualUndoListViewTouchListener. #1.
Added a check so only instances of ContextualUndoView are swipeable.  Allowing for mixing of view types with some un-dissmissible
Added support for auto deletion after a delay when an item is removed by swipe, and two example activities
Removed TextSwitcher and CountDownTimer, now uses Handler.postDelayed().
Fixed NullPointerException in getView of ContextualUndoAdapter
Added option to set initial delay of AnimationAdapter
Possible fix for double dismissing positions
Added option to start animations from a certain position. Fixes #31.
Added option to specify the resource id of a View that will be the expand / collapse animation actuator. Fixes #33.
Update the virtual list count when the data set is changed. Fixes #30.
Added option to swipe a view at given position. Fixes #17
streetsofboston: "Added DynamicLlistView for dragging and dropping list-items. ListViews can now be in horizontal scroll containers and still behave as expected."
Don't call getItemId with impossible values
Added default swapItems(int, int) implementation to ArrayAdapter
Be able to dedicate a child inside a list-item that the user can target to start swiping or dragging.

When the user is swiping and then moving upwards or downwards (vertically), the swipe suddenly changed into a drag&drop. Thiis has sometimes strange consequences. Instead, when the user is swiping, never stop swiping until the user releases his/her finger.
Allow the hover-cell (i.e. the list-item being dragged) to be custom drawn through a callback.
add newline for github not to cry
dispatch code in different functions to help override
Added option to limit the number of expanded items to 1.
Extended limit to an arbitrary value. Fixes #52.
update project so it can be build with latest android studio
Fixed link for StickyListHeader as the github page doesn't exist
Removed StickyListHeaders references - it is not used anymore
Re-introduced issue #5 to fix a more serious bug where items would disappear when recycling a view for the same position. Fixes #51
Fix expanded items not expanded after recycle. Fixes #50.
Fixed positions callback on swipe to dismiss and animate dismiss. Fixes #54
Fixed drag&drop with headers in the listview. Fixes #43.
Added methods to provide animation timings. Fixes #59
Fix for not initializing mExpandedViews. Fixes #69
Add method to let to know if a position is expanded
Scroll when the expand view isn't visible
Touch Child was never 'activated'. (cherry picked from commit 91b0ce2) (cherry picked from commit e7c4550)
The 'Current Removed View' was never permanently removed (Android 4.3)
Making the content and undo views INVISIBLE instead of GONE prevents some strange layout issues.
Allow users of ContextualUndoAdapters to forcefully remove any pending item. (cherry picked from commit e17bb2a)
Fix issues related to recycling ContextualUndoViews as list-items related to animations. (cherry picked from commit ff921c2)
Fix issues related to recycling ContextualUndoViews as list-items related to animations. (cherry picked from commit f93da8a)
Added ItemMovedListener. Listener to get noticed after item is completely moved by drag and drop.
Added methods for programmatically expand / collapse items: expand(int), collapse(int), toggle(int). Fixes #77.
Added methods for programmatically expand / collapse items: expand(int), collapse(int), toggle(int). Fixes #77.
Renamed package com.haarman to com.nhaarman to reflect maven hosting
Modified maven_push to publish jar file
Fixed bug where a header view's tag would be wrongly cast to ViewHolder
Removed saving references to views -- possible leak. Fix #96
Check a DeleteItemCallback is set before accessing it. Fixes #105
Enforce providing a DeleteItemCallback when creating a new ContextualUndoAdapter. Fixes #111
Use consistent indentation (4 spaces instead of tabs). Fix 106.

Created AdapterViewUtil#getPositionForView(AdapterView, View) which should be used instead of directly calling AdapterView#getPositionForView to take headerviews into account.  (Note: DynamicListView does not use this method). Fixes #105
We're only measuring GridView items if we're actually showing a GridView. Possible fix for #112.
SwipeDismissAdapter should not count header view into removed positions
Consider padding when scrolling ListView in ExpandableListItemAdapter
Added methods to cancel and remove pending items
Fixed crash when transcript mode was enabled. Fixes #98.
Made ArrayAdapter implement List, use the given list reference as default.
Created InsertQueue, AnimateAddition uses this queue
Don't snap when inserting items that aren't visible
Check animation duration type based on number of animated items instead of last animated item. Fixes #129.
Properly measure a expanding content view. Fixes #61.
Fixed small jump in expandable list items example
Removed unnecessary support library; updated support v7 version
Fixed crash when dragging (over) header and footer views
Use a more robust way of checking if GridView is measuring an item. Fixes #137.
Fixed crash when the listview has footerViews
Fixed crash when trying to drag into a footer

BaseAdapterDecorator cleanup, deprecated methods and added alternates
Extracted base functionality of SwipeDismissTouchListener into SwipeTouchListener
Added methods to programmatically initiate a fling or dismiss
Removed contextual undo package, fixed copyright statements

Fixed animation if the listview isn't filled completely yet
Added option to save instance state to animationadapter
Fix first GridView item animation on KitKat

Only publish if no pull request
